annotationA: Ubiquitin specific protease 14 (Usp14) is a deubiquitinase that associates with the 19S component of the proteasome in a reversible manner. Usp14 functions include ubiquitin chain disassemblance for mono-ubiquitin recycling, control of protein degradation by the proteasome and regulation of proteasome subtrate interactions; Belongs to the peptidase C19 family
annotationB: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 3-related, isoform C; ATP binding; ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proteolysis; cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; protein catabolic process
